D:
Ngo korin itan ‘yanu na;
Ti jesu t’oku fun mi;
B’o ti fi ‘le ogo sile,
Fun iku abgelebu.

Chorus:
Ngo maa korin ‘tan ‘yanu na
Ti Jesu t’o ku fun mi;
Ngo b’awon mimo korin na,
‘Gbat’a ba pade loke.

Jesu mbo! Ko oro ayo na;
 Mbo fawon to feje re rapada,
 Mbo lati joba b’oluwa ogo;
Jesu yo tun pada wa:

Chorus;
Jesu yo tun wa, yo tun pada wa
Jesu yo tun pada wa 
Ho iho ayo n aka bi gbogbo
Jesu yo tun pada wa.

Ni akoko ikehin yi,
Itunu nla n’ireti na;
Pe jesu tun npada bow a;
O mbo wa lati joba gbogb’ aiye

Chorus:
O npada bo, o npada bo,
Awa y’o fi ayo pade Re;
L’ooro l’ale l’osan tabi l’orun,
Jesu y’o de laipe

C:
Oh, Joy! Oh delight! Should we go without dying;
No sickness, no sadness, no dread and no crying;
Caught up through the clouds with our
Lord into glory
When Jesus receives “His own”  
[Chorus]

Whosoever cometh need not delay;
Now the door is open, enter while you may;
Jesus is the true and only Living Way,
“Whosoever will may come”.
[Chorus]

Whosoever will” the promise is secure;
“Whosoever will,” forever shall endure;
 “Whosoever will”- ‘tis life evermore;
“Whosoever will may come”.
[Chorus]

Oh! escape to yonder mountain,
Refuge find in Him to-day;
Christ invites you to the fountain,
Come and wash your sins away;
Do not tarry, do not tarry,
Come to Jesus while you may,

Grace is flowing like a river,
Millions there have been supplied;
Still it flows as fresh as ever,
From the Saviour’s wounded side;
None need perish, None need perish
All may live, for Christ hath died.

Christ alone shall be out portion;
Soon we hope to meet above;
Then we’ll bathe in the full ocean
Of the great Redeemer’s love;
All His fullness, All His fullness,
We shall then forever prove.

I have a precious Saviour, He came from heav-n-above;
And died from me on Cal-va-ry, To prove
His match-less love;
This love so free-ly giv-en, He offers now to you;
Won’t you let my Saviour be your Saviour too?
Chorus: 
Won’t you let Him be your Saviour too?
He would prove a faithful friend to you;
He would puri-fy your soul, keep you
Ever pure and whole
Won’t you let my Saviour be your Saviour too?

I have a long Saviour, He hears me when I call;
He helps to bear each load of care, And
Lifts me when I fall;
So kind is He, so tender, Com-pas-sion-ate and true;
Won’t you let my Saviour be your Saviour too?
[Chorus]

D:
B’ O bap on mi L’oju,
Ninu ife Re;
Da ibukun Re le,
Ori ebon a;
Ki nf’ ara mi fun O,
Lori pepe Re;
B’ara ko ogo na,
Igbagbo y’o mu.

Ranti awa t’o nrahun,
T’a won agbelebu Re;
F’ireti mimo fun wa;
     Jesu, sanu fun wa.

Ki gbogbo awa Tire
Je omo ile kanna;
‘Tori Re k’a fe ‘ra wa;
     Jseu, sanu fun wa.

‘Gbati a ba npe lasan,
T’ireti wa si jina;
N’nu ookun na di wa mu;
     Jesu, sanu fun wa.

C:
Thirst for us in mercy still;
All your holy work fulfill;
Satisfy your loving will:
Hear us, holy Jesus.

D:
Maa kongbe fun wa sibe,
Sise mimo l’ara wa;
Te ife Re na l’orun;
     Jesu, sanu fun wa.

Jesu, gbogbo ise Re,
Gbogbo ijamu Re pin;
O jow’ emi Re lowo;
     Jesu, sanu fun wa.

‘Gbati ‘ku ba de ba wa,
Gba wa lowo ota wa;
Yo wa ni wakati na;
     Jesu, sanu fun wa.

C:
A ruler once came to Jesus by night,
To ask Him the way of salvation and light;
The Master made answers in words true and plain;

Chorus: 
Ye must be born again,
Ye must be born again;
I verily, verily say unto thee,
Ye must be born again;

D:
Okan mi; ‘Wo y’o se lo
Kuro lod’ Ore yi,
Sa sunmo timo-timo;
Baa gbe titi d’opin,
O se: ailera mi po,
Mo kun f’ese pupo;
N’tor’ emi ko le sako;
Lehin mo ba pada.
    Wa, wa sodo Mi &c.

C:
Make us gentle, meek, and humble,
And yet bold in doing right;
Scatter darkness, lest we stumble;
Men walk safely in the light.

D:
Se wa l’eni tutu, pele,
K’a maa f’igbaiya s’ooto;
L’ookun lo, k’a ma se kose;
Ko s’ewu lojojumo.

Jesu n’ise Olugbala,
Jesu l’  Oluwa wa;
Igbala wa li owo Re;
Fun awa elese.

Wa nisisiyi, wa toro,
Ife wa ninu Re;
Enyin ti o buru l’ O npe;
E wa gba igbala.

C:
‘Twas most impossible of all
That here sin’s reign in me should cease;
Yet shall it be, I know it shall;
Jesus, I trust Thy faithfulness!
If nothing is too hard for Thee,
All things are possible to me.

 Though earth and hell the word gainsay,
The word of god shall never fail;
The Lord can break sin’s iron sway;
‘Tis certain, though impossible
The thing impossible shall be,
All things are possible to me.

D:
B’aiye ba kegan Oro na,
Oro Olorun ko le ye;
Iwo nfo agbara ese,
O daju pe iwo le se;
Ko s’ohun t’o soro fun O,
Sise l’ohun gbogbo fun mi.

C:
All things are possible to God;
To Christ, the power of God in man;
To me when I am all renewed;
In Christ am fully formed again,
And from the reign of sin set free.
All things are possible to me.

D:
Sise l’ohun gbogbo fun O
Fun Krist’ agbara Olorun;
Fun mi ‘gbati mo d’atunbi,
Ti mo si di eda titun;
Ese ko le bori mi mo,
Sise l’ohun gbogbo fun mi.

C:
All things are possible to God,
To Christ, the power of God in me;
Now shed Thy mighty self abroad,
Let me no longer live, but Thee;
Give me this hour in Thee to prove
The sweet omnipotence of love.

D:
Sise l’ohun gbogbo fun O;
Fun Krist’ agbara ninu mi;
Tan ogo imole Re  ka,
Ki nma wa fun ara mi mo,
Ki nfihan lat’ isisiyi,
Sise l’ohun gbogbo fun mi.

C:
I must needs go home by the way of the cross,
There’s no other way but this;
I shall ne’er get sight of the Gates of light
If the way of the cross I miss.

Chorus: 
The way of the cross leads home;
The way of the cross leads home;
It is sweet to know, as I on-ward go,
The way of the cross leads home.

O grant that nothing in my soul
May dwell but Thy pure love alone;
O may Thy love possess me whole,
My joy, my treasure, and my crown:
Strange flames far from my heart remove;
My every act, world, thought, be love.

D:
Mase jeki ohunkohun
Gba mi l’okan ju ‘re Re lo;
K’ife Re gba gbogb’ okan mi
K’o j’ayo, ‘sura, ade mi!
Mu ‘fekufe jinna si mi;
K’ife j’oro at’ise mi.

C:
Unwearied may I this pursue,
Dauntless to the high prize aspire;
Hourly within my soul renew
This holy flame, this heavenly fire;
And day and night be all my care.
To guard the sacred treasure there.

D:
 Je ki nmma lepa ife yi,
At’ere giga,l’aisaare;
So ina mimo yi d’otun,
N’nu emi mi lojojumo,
K’ajo mi, losan loru je;
Lati so ‘sura owo na.

Mo fe O n’gbagbogbo,
‘Wo Ologo julo;
Se mi n’Tire ‘tooto;
Omo Alabukun.
Mo fe O, etc.

To wa l’ojo gbogbo, l’ona t’awa nto,
Mu wan so s’isegun l’ori ota wa;
K’Angel’ Re s’asa wa gb’oju orun su;
Dariji, si gba wa lakoko iku,
    Didun l’opagun wa &c.

Mo ntesiwaju l’ona na,
Mo ngoke si lojojumo;
Mo ngbadura bi mo tin lo;
Oluwa, jo gbe mi soke.

Chorus:
Oluwa, jo gbe mi soke,
Fa mi lo si ibi giga;
Apata t’o ga ju mi lo,
Oluwa, jo gbe mi soke.

C:
More about Jesus, on His throne,
Riches in glory all His own;
More of His kingdom’s sure increase;
More of His coming, Prince of Peace.
[Chorus]

Come to Him believing, Harken to His call;
Yield to Him your all; 
Jesus will accept you
When to Him you flee; 
He will grant His blessing More abundantly.

D:
Lekan oju mi ti fo s’ogo Oluwa,
Lekan eti mi ti di s’ohun oro Re;
Lekan mo te ade egun moo li ori;
Sugbon O ti dariji mi, ko tun si nkan mo.

Chorus:
Ko si nkan mo, beni ko si nkan mo,
O ti gbo adura mi, ko si nkan;
Ko si nkan mo, beni ko si nkan mo;
O ti bo gbogb’ ese mi, ko tun si nkan.

Ohun rere ni lati wa l’odo Jesu,
‘Gbati ‘danwo de ti oju mi si Sookun;
Ki nsa ri owo ife Re li ori mi;
Ki nsi gbo ohun jeje Re wipe, ki si nkan.
[Chorus]

C:
Take, my soul, Thy full salvation;
Rise o’er sin, and fear, and care;
Joy to find in every station
Something still to do or bear:
Think what Spirit dwells within thee;
What a Father’s smile in Thine;
What a Saviour died to win thee;
Child of heaven, shouldst thou repine?

D:
Okan mi, gba igbala re,
Bori ese at’eru;
F’ayo wa ni ipokipo,
Maa sise, si ma jiya:
Ro t’Emi t’o wa ninu re;
At’ ife Baba si o;
W’Olugbala t’o ku fun O;
Omo orun, mase kun!

Iwo l’Ooto; Oro Tire;
L’o le f’ogbon fun wa;
Iwo nikan l’o le ko wa,
T’O si le we okan.

C:
“There shall be showers of blessings”
Promise that never can fail;
Thou wilt regard our petition;
Surely our faith will prevail.
[Chorus]

I have a Shepherd, One I love so well;
How he has blessed me tongue can never tell;
On the cross He suffered, shed His blood and died,
That I might ever in His love confide.

Chorus:
Following Jesus, ever day by day,
Nothing can harm me when He leads the way;
Darkness or sunshine, what-e’er befall,
Jesus, the Shepherd, is my All in All.

Blessed is the service of our Lord and King,
Precious are the jewels we may help to bring;
Down the passing ages words of counsel ring,
He that winneth souls is wise;

Chorus:
He that winneth souls is wise;
In  the home beyond the skies
There’s a crown of glory, oh, the wondrous prize!
He that winneth souls is wise.

Go out in the by-ways and search them all;
The wheat may be there, though the weeds are tall;
Then search in the highway and pass none by,
But gather from all for the home on high.
[Chorus]

D:
O ti dun to lati rohin Re,
Lati so ti Jesu f’elomi;
K’a ba le dariji elese,
K’a si fi Krist t’a kan mo ‘gi han won;
Ayo okan wa ti po to,
‘Gbat’ elese ronupiwada;
Ti asako pada bo wa ‘le,
Ti okunkun re si di imole.

Chorus:
Oruko didun ti Jesu,
Oruko ti a nfe julo ni;
Orin t’o dun julo ni l’eti,
Orin mi ni l’osan ati l’oru.

Nigbose orin irapada
L’ao ma ko l’oke l’awosanma;
Y’o de bi Oba lati pew a;
Kuro laiye nibit’ O ku fun wa;
Gbogbo awon t’a rapada
Y’o pejo l’ese Reni sanma
Gbogbo won y’o ko Halleluya,
Ao korin ‘gba ba pade Oluwa.

C:
A shade by day, defence by night;
A shelter in the time of storm!
No fears alarm, no foes affright;
A shelter in the time of storm!
[Chorus]

D:
Nigbamiran Oluwa,
Nyo lojiji si wa;
Imole kan a si tan,
Pelu orin iyin;
‘Gbat’ o dabi enipe,
Itunu kan ko si;
Y’o tu okan wa lara,
Bi ojo lat’orun.

C:
In holy contemplation,
We sweetly then pursue
The theme of God’s salvation,
And find it ever new;
Set free from present sorrow;
We cheerfully can say,
E’en let th’unknown to-morrow
Bring with it what it may;

D:
Pelu isaro didun,
A ranti ife Re;
Igbala nla n’nu Jesu,
Otun ni titi lai;
Eyi le ‘banuje lo,
O nmu okan way o;
B’a ko tile mo ola,
A n’ireti didun.

C:
It can bring with it nothing
But He will bear us through;
Who gives the lilies clothing
Will clothe His people too;
Beneath the spreading heavens
No creatures but is fed;
And He who feeds the ravens
Will give His children bread.

D:
B’ajara tab’opoto,
Ko tile so eso;
Bi gbogb’ oko tile ro,
T’agbo eran segbe;
Olorun mbe bakanna,
Ngo nkorin iyin Re;
Bi mo ti ngbekele mi le E,
Ayo mi y’o ma po.

Ife Kristi alailegbe,
Ore-ofe iyanu;
Anu Re ga ju orun lo;
O si jin ju okun lo.
[Chorus]

Iwenu ati iwosanmbe;
F’awont’o we ninu eje na;
Ayo at’iye ainipekun,
Low’ otun Olorun nikehin.
[Chorus]
